# ioBroker.motioneye

Connects ioBroker to a local [MotionEye](https://github.com/motioneye-project/motioneye) server for camera motion detection, snapshots, and MJPEG streams.

## Stack

- Plain **JavaScript** in `main.js` — no TypeScript build step; type hints via JSDoc + `admin/adapter-config.d.ts`
- Admin UI via **jsonConfig** (`admin/jsonConfig.json`), not a compiled React frontend
- HTTP: native `node:http` (no axios/request)
- MotionEye logic in `lib/` (`motionEyeApi`, `modeProfiles`, `streamManager`, `webhookServer`, `cameraRegistry`)

## Git (mandatory)

- **Never** run `git commit`, `git push`, or releases unless the user explicitly asks
- User commits and pushes; releases via `npm run release-*` (AlCalzone release-script)
- **Never** run `npm run translate` — owner runs it manually before release

## Changelog & README (mandatory for every change)

For **every code or config change**, update `README.md` before finishing:

1. Add a user-facing entry under `### **WORK IN PROGRESS**` (English)
2. Format: `- (author) Plain description` — no bold prefixes (`**FIXED**`, `**NEW**`, etc.; breaks news translation)
3. Update README sections (Installation, Configuration, Usage) when behavior or options change
4. Do **not** edit `CHANGELOG_OLD.md` manually — release-script moves older entries there

## Scope

- Minimal, focused diffs; match patterns in `main.js` and `lib/`
- After every code change: run `npm run lint` and fix all warnings (CI uses `--max-warnings 0`)

## Local checks (optional, matches CI)

- `npm run lint`
- `npm run test`

## Further rules

Detailed conventions live in `.cursor/rules/` (code, admin UI, testing, docs/CI, MotionEye patterns).

